<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1011: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-07T17:00:00-05:00">December 7, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>12. For Corrigan. Your no. 32, December 6, 1 p.m. and 33, December 6,
                                8 p.m. In view of the expressed willingness of the Nicaraguan
                                delegation to waive insistence on point 6 you are authorized in your
                                discretion to agree to its elimination if in your judgement it is
                                essential in order to expedite signature of the agreement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>